{
  "abstract": "A procedure has been described to determine picomole levels\r\nof adenosine3',5'-cyclic monophosphate (CAMP) in plant materials. The purification of CAMP from other\r\ninterfering nucleotide and phenolic compounds is made\r\nusing paper and column chromatography. The resulting CAMP\r\nis enzymatically transformed to ATP and estimated by its luminescent reaction with iuciferase. The advantages of this method have been discussed in the light of purification and assay of CAMP. The content of CAMP in lettuce, barley seeds, cabbage leaves, and cultivated mushrooms has been estimated by this procedure",
